# Route Page Composition

For files matching `src/app/**/page.tsx`:

- Build the route UI directly in the `page.tsx` file.
- Do not create route-specific wrapper components under `src/components/*` just to render them from the page.
- Prefer imports from `@ui` for reusable primitives and from shared modules/components.
- Avoid page imports that point to route-specific presentational wrappers.

## Preferred pattern

```tsx
// src/app/(customer)/requests/page.tsx
'use client'

import { Heading, Stack } from '@ui'

export default function CustomerRequestsPage() {
  return (
    <Stack>
      <Heading size="xl">My requests</Heading>
    </Stack>
  )
}
```

## Avoid

```tsx
// page only proxies another route-specific view component
import { CustomerRequestsView } from '@/components/customer/CustomerRequestsView'

export default function CustomerRequestsPage() {
  return <CustomerRequestsView />
}
```
